Here's a function that does what you're looking for:

```julia
using Dates

function add_yearmonth(df::DataFrame)
    df.ym = DateTime.(df.dt) |> yearmonth |> int
    return df
end

function yearmonth(dt::DateTime)
    return Dates.DateTime(Dates.year(dt), Dates.month(dt))
end

function int(dt::DateTime)
    return Dates.value(dt)
end
```

The `add_yearmonth` function takes a `DataFrame` as input and adds a new column `ym` by extracting the year and month from the `dt` column. It uses two helper functions, `yearmonth` and `int`, to extract the year and month and convert the result to an integer.
